modules.description: This module implements version control operations for managing Git objects, including hashing, filtering, and dumping commit data. It works with Git trees, files, and hashes, using a customizable storage backend via the `S` module. Concrete use cases include reconstructing directory structures from Git commits and filtering files based on extension during tree traversal.

This module implements version control operations for managing Git objects such as trees, files, and hashes, supporting actions like hashing, filtering, and dumping commit data. It uses a customizable storage backend and enables tasks like reconstructing directory structures from commits and filtering files by extension during tree traversal.

This module provides functions for hashing Git objects, traversing and filtering trees by file extension, and reconstructing directory structures from commit data. It works with Git trees, files, and hashes, using a customizable storage backend. Concrete use cases include dumping commit contents to disk and filtering version-controlled files during tree traversal.
